Valuable as Carte’s publication undoubtedly is, and interesting as it may have been to France¹‚ yet it is a very imperfect work3 for it does not refer to even a tenth part of the documents enrolled. It must, however, be said, in

ustice to Carte, that he merely printed the calendars² which he found in the Tower3 and that he was induced to do so from a feeling of gratitude for the kindness he had experienced during six years residence in France; facts which ought to remove from that eminent writer the reproach of having published so incomplete a work.
